x4freetext: EXperiment performed using K500
cyclotron facility at Texas A&M University
The reaction products were detected in
an array of four Si E-dE telescopes located in a
plane 14 cm downstream of the target. The
telescopes, part of the High Resolution Array,
consisted of a 65 mu-m thick, single-sided Si-strip
dE detector followed by a 1.5-mm-thick, double-sided
Si strip E detector.All Si detectors were 6.4 x 6.4
cm2 in area with their position-sensitive faces
divided into 32 strips.
Primary beam of 10B at E/A = 15.0 MeV impinged on a
hydrogen gas cell held at a pressure of 2 atm and
kept at liquid-nitrogen temperature.A secondary beam
of 10C with energy of E/A = 10.7 MeV was produced
through the 10B(p,n)10C reaction and separated from
other reaction products using the momentum achromat
recoil spectrometer MARS.
